{
  "texts": [
    "However, they give rise to known examples.",
    "Proposition 3.8.",
    "Let (M, g, X) be an expanding Ricci soliton obtained from a solution (g B, ρ, h) to the twisted harmonic-Einstein equations (20) with totally geodesic h. Then, the universal cover ( M, g) is the Riemannian product of a homogeneous Ricci soliton and an Einstein manifold.Proof.",
    "To begin with, assume that h is an immersion.",
    "Observe that h is necessarily an injective immersion: if h b1 = h b2 then h sends any geodesic in B that joints b 1 to b 2 to a geodesic in G/K that starts and ends at the same point."
